          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Situation A. More Claims</strong></p>",
            "Ms. Cho’s students also made the following claims. Do you agree? Explain why.",
            "<strong>Mitch’s Claim</strong> All squares are similar."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Yes. The corresponding angles will be 90˚. For corresponding side lengths, you can always find a scale factor. Adjacent sides will always be equivalent ratios of side to side.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<strong>Freda’s Claim</strong> All circles are similar."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Yes. All circles are the same shape. Any radius can be scaled to find a corresponding radius. Any diameter can be scaled to find a corresponding diameter.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<strong>Juan’s Claim</strong> All quadrilaterals are similar."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>No. All of the following shapes are quadrilaterals. None of them are similar to the other.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "display": "teacher",
        "id": "YBpMcjE1W-Ha652l",
        "title": "Examples of non-similar quadrilaterals",
        "content": {
