        }
      },
      {
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<strong>Sze’s Claim</strong> All triangles are similar if their corresponding angles are equal."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Yes. If all of the angles have equivalent measures, the triangles will have the same basic shape. The corresponding side lengths can be scaled to form a similar triangle.</p>",
            "<p>We saw this idea when we had reptiles.</p>",
            "<p>And we used this idea when   measuring the river.</p>"
          ]
        }
